This Python code uses the TensorFlow and Keras libraries to build and train a CNN model for bone fracture detection.

Prerequisites: Install the necessary libraries and have a dataset of X-ray images.

                pip install tensorflow opencv-python numpy scikit-learn matplotlib

Dataset: You need a dataset of X-ray images with separate folders for fractured and non-fractured bones. 
        A common publicly available dataset is the MURA (Musculoskeletal Radiographs) dataset from Stanford University. 
        For this code to work, organize your data like this:data/
data/
├── train/
│   ├── fractured/
│   │   ├── img1.png
│   │   ├── img2.png
│   │   └── ...
│   └── non-fractured/
│       ├── img3.png
│       ├── img4.png
│       └── ...
└── test/
    ├── fractured/
    │   └── ...
    └── non-fractured/
        └── ...

        Python Script:bone_fracture_detection.py


        
